y) in relation to some of the quirkiest literary and visual material to be found in early modern culture, it will also appeal to a wider audience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAbnormalities, Human, in art. 0aAbnormalities, Human, in literature. 0aEnglish literaturexHistory and criticismyEarly modern, 1500-1700. 0aEuropean literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aUgliness in art. 0aUgliness in literature. 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aEnglish drama.  aEuropean visual art.  aSilenus figures.  acompelling art.  aearly modern English culture.  amasculine identity.  amodels of identity.  atwelfth-century German kingdom.  augly woman.  aunattractive human body.  aunattractive mistresses English literature.1 aBaker, Naomi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526129680423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526129680/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles